# Prompt Builder Rules — build-prompts.js

## Overview
`build-prompts.js` is the single source of all prompt assembly logic. Every string that gets sent to the Claude API passes through here. Getting this wrong silently degrades takeoff accuracy.

---

## Exported Functions — What Each One Does

| Function | Used By | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `buildSystemPrompt()` | Standalone takeoff route | Default prompt, no knowledge base |
| `buildCustomProjectSystemPrompt(planType)` | Project launch-takeoff route | Full tier hierarchy prompt |
| `buildKeynoteRegisterPrompt()` | `runTakeoffCivil()` Pass 1 | Extracts keynote register from first page |
| `buildSheetTakeoffPrompt(keynoteRegister, pageNum, totalPages, useCustomProject)` | `runTakeoffCivil()` Pass 2 | Per-sheet takeoff with register injected |

Do **not** merge these functions. Each serves a distinct flow.

---

## `buildCustomProjectSystemPrompt(planType)` — Mandatory Assembly Order

This function MUST assemble the prompt in this exact order. Changing the order degrades accuracy.

```javascript
function buildCustomProjectSystemPrompt(planType = 'auto') {
  let prompt = '';

  // 1. TIER 1 — Always first, always present (TIER1_FILES constant)
  prompt += assembleTierBlock('TIER 1 — BURT OVERRIDES (supersede all rules below)', TIER1_FILES);

  // 2. Project instructions
  prompt += '\n\n' + readFile('instructions.txt');

  // 3. TIER 2 — Process methodology (TIER2_CONTEXT constant)
  prompt += assembleTierBlock('TIER 2 — PROCESS INSTRUCTIONS', TIER2_CONTEXT);

  // 4. TIER 3 + shared — files listed for this planType in plan-type-docs.js
  const docList = getPlanTypeDocs(planType); // reads from plan-type-docs.js DOC_MAP
  prompt += assembleTierBlock(`TIER 3 — ${planType.toUpperCase()} REFERENCE RULES`, docList);

  // 5. Output format block — Always last
  prompt += buildOutputFormatBlock();

  return prompt;
}
```

> **Implementation note:** The actual codebase uses fixed file-name arrays (`TIER1_FILES`, `TIER2_CONTEXT`) and a `plan-type-docs.js` doc map for tier 3, pulling content from `knowledge-cache.js` by filename. It does **not** scan tier subfolders dynamically. The `buildTierBlock` pattern described in earlier design docs was the intended architecture — the current implementation achieves the same result via explicit file lists. When adding new reference files, add them to the appropriate constant or `DOC_MAP` entry, not just to the folder.

---

## File List Constants — Where Doc Lists Live

| Constant / Source | What it controls |
|------------------|-----------------|
| `TIER1_FILES` (in `build-prompts.js`) | Always-injected Burt Override files |
| `TIER2_CONTEXT` (in `build-prompts.js`) | Always-injected process methodology files |
| `DOC_MAP` (in `plan-type-docs.js`) | Per-plan-type file lists for tier 3 + shared |

**To add a new reference document:**
1. Place the file in the correct `knowledge/tier*/` subfolder
2. Add its filename to the appropriate constant or `DOC_MAP` entry in `plan-type-docs.js`
3. Warm the cache — new files are picked up at server restart automatically if `knowledge-cache.js` reads the full knowledge tree

---

## `buildOutputFormatBlock()` — Always Last in Prompt

This block closes every custom project prompt. It MUST be the final content Claude sees before the user message.

```javascript
function buildOutputFormatBlock() {
  return `

${'='.repeat(60)}
OUTPUT FORMAT REQUIREMENTS
${'='.repeat(60)}

Return ONLY valid JSON matching the material takeoff schema.
Do not include any text outside the JSON object.
Do not include markdown code fences.
The response must begin with { and end with }.

Confidence levels: "high" = measurable from plans, "medium" = estimated with reasonable basis, "low" = assumed or missing data.
Flag any item where quantity cannot be determined from provided plans.
`;
}
```

