## Two New Functions Required for Civil Pass System

### `buildKeynoteRegisterPrompt()`
- Used in Pass 1 of the civil flow (page 1 only)
- Instructs Claude to return ONLY a JSON keynote register
- Must include: sheet names, scale per sheet, keynote-to-material mapping
- Must NOT request quantities — Pass 1 is register extraction only

```javascript
function buildKeynoteRegisterPrompt() {
  return `
You are analyzing the first page of a civil engineering plan set.
Extract and return ONLY a JSON keynote register with this structure:

{
  "project_name": "string",
  "sheets": [
    { "sheet_number": "C-101", "title": "string", "scale": "1\" = 20'" }
  ],
  "keynote_legend": [
    { "keynote": "1", "material": "string", "spec": "string" }
  ],
  "notes": "string"
}

Return ONLY the JSON. No other text.
`;
}
```

### `buildSheetTakeoffPrompt(keynoteRegister, pageNum, totalPages, useCustomProject)`
- Used in Pass 2 of the civil flow (one call per sheet)
- Injects the keynote register from Pass 1 as context
- Instructs Claude to take off THIS SHEET ONLY
- Must include warning: "Do not count items from other sheets"
- If `useCustomProject` is true, prepend the full tier hierarchy

---

## What NOT to Put in build-prompts.js

- No file I/O other than reading knowledge base files via cache
- No Anthropic API calls — those belong in `takeoff.js`
- No business logic (saving results, project lookups)
- No hardcoded quantities or material prices
- No inline knowledge content — always read from files

---

## Pollution Prevention Checklist

Before committing any change to `build-prompts.js`, verify:

- [ ] No `.py`, `.js`, `.ts`, `.json` files are being injected into prompts
- [ ] `tier1-overrides` is still the first block in custom project prompts
- [ ] `buildOutputFormatBlock()` is still the last block
- [ ] `buildSystemPrompt()` does NOT read from the knowledge base
- [ ] `buildCustomProjectSystemPrompt()` does NOT call `buildSystemPrompt()`
- [ ] No file is read twice (cache hit should prevent this)
- [ ] `planType` defaults to `'auto'` → `tier3-residential` when unrecognized

---

## Adding a New Plan Type

1. Create `knowledge/tier3-{newtype}/` and populate with reference files
2. Add a `DOC_MAP.{newtype}` entry in `plan-type-docs.js` listing the files to inject
3. Add entry to plan type selector in `LaunchTakeoffWidget.tsx`
4. Add entry to `planType` handling in `server/routes/projects.js`
5. Decide if it needs a custom takeoff flow in `takeoff.js` (like civil does)
6. Update `takeoff-architecture.mdc` Plan Type Values table
